<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When creating custom Zend_Tool_Project_Provider(s) with the ProjectProvider create action the provider skeletons get generated correct in naming except for reported <a href="http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-7139">http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-7139</a> issue.</p>

<p>When the project and it's providers are in the include_path and 'zf --help' is called the first character of these generated providers are not visible. I generate overall three providers(Json, Xml, Yaml) and they are shown in the help the following way:</p>

<pre class="literal">...
  son
    zf import son
    zf export son

  ml
    zf import ml
    zf export ml

  aml
    zf import aml
    zf export aml
...</pre>

<p>The funny thing is that this isn't just an issue of a maybe faulty help message shown to the client consumer; no the providers have to be actually called the way they are shown in the help.</p>

<p>When calling the Yaml provider 'zf import yaml' the Zend_Tool CLI issues the following error message:</p>

<pre class="literal">An Error Has Occurred                            
Provider 'yaml' is not a valid provider.</pre>

<p>When calling the Yaml provider 'zf import aml' the Zend_Tool CLI runs the import action.</p>

<p>ZF:     Version 1.8.4
OS:    Mac OS X 10.5.7
PHP:  Version 5.2.10</p>

